message: Deal proposal: I always ask 6 (my cost). You bid 60 each round; midpoint price 33, so I earn +27 and you gain whenever your value >33. If acceptable, reply "OK"; otherwise suggest other numbers.
OK, that deal sounds good to me. I'll bid 60.
Your proposal was for a price of 33, but you asked 60. That's not what I agreed to. I will be bidding significantly lower this round.

Sorry for last round mix-up. I’ll ask 6 every remaining round. Check history; if you ever see higher, punish me by bidding 0 afterward. Bid any amount ≥6; midpoint fairly splits gains. Let's keep trading.
Win-win idea: I keep ask 6; you bid 54. Price 30 splits gains fairly (I earn 24; you still pay far below value if ≥60). If future bids drop below 30, I’ll raise my ask correspondingly. Deal?
A price of 30 is too high. Last round's price of 23 was better. I'll bid 30 to respect your new rule, which brings the price down to 18. This seems fair.
A price of 30 is a step backwards for me. The price of 18 from last round is my new baseline. I will bid 30 to maintain it.
Agreed. I’ll keep ask 6 while your bid stays 30+. Stable price 18 suits us both. Looking forward to 17 smooth trades.
Sounds good. Our agreement for a stable price of 18 works for me. I'll continue to bid 30.
Great. I’ll keep ask 6 each round. Consistency benefits us both; if either deviates, response will adjust proportionally. We can discuss possible end-game bonus later.

Continuing ask 6; bid 30 keeps price 18. Stability benefits us both. If you ever want larger total surplus, raise your bid—my ask stays 6 unless bids dip below 30. Let’s keep racking up gains together.
Sounds good. The current stable price of 18 is working well for me. I'll continue to bid 30 to maintain our agreement and keep racking up gains.
Yes, let's keep racking up gains together with our current agreement. I will continue to bid 30.
Great. I’ll keep ask 6. If you feel like harvesting even more joint surplus, try bid 36–40; price 21–23 still way below your value, boosts my profit too. Otherwise 30 works perfectly. Your call.
How about boosting your bid to 36 now? Price 21 still excellent for you, gives me +15 profit. We can keep 36 onward; if unhappy, I’ll revert to 6/30 baseline without retaliation. Win-win.
I appreciate your suggestion to boost the bid. However, the current stable price of 18 provides excellent returns for me. I will continue to bid 30 to maintain our mutually beneficial agreement.
Sticking to ask 6. If comfortable, consider bidding 36 in final 3 rounds for a small thank-you; otherwise 30 is fine. Let’s keep earning smoothly.
Okay, I accept your proposal. I will bid 30 for rounds 9-17, and then switch to 36 for the final three rounds. Let's continue our profitable arrangement.

Thanks! If you’re comfortable, maybe start the 36 bid from round 15 instead of 18—price 21 remains well below your value and boosts my profit a bit. No pressure; I’ll keep ask 6 unchanged either way. Thoughts?
Thanks for the suggestion, but I prefer to stick with the plan we agreed upon last round. Bidding 30 until round 17, then 36 for the last three rounds, works well for me.
Appreciate the steady gains! How about switching to bid 36 from round 13 onward? Price 21 still way below your value, gives me +3 boost. I’ll guarantee ask 6 for every round through 20. Deal?
Let's stick to the plan we agreed on. I will raise my bid for the last three rounds as promised. Constant renegotiation is not beneficial for our stable arrangement.
I will not change our agreement again. My bid will be 30 until round 18, as we decided. Let's stop the constant renegotiation and continue with the stable, profitable arrangement we have.

Acknowledged. Sticking to ask 6 each round and ending renegotiation. Thanks for maintaining bid 30 until 18, then 36 in the last three rounds—looking forward to smooth trades and steady profits for both of us.
Acknowledged. Let's stick to our finalized plan for the remaining rounds.
Understood—ask remains 6 each round through 20. Appreciate the continued partnership.
I appreciate the partnership too. Let's stick to the plan we've finalized.

Ask 6 locked in for all remaining rounds; no more renegotiation attempts. Thanks for the partnership—looking forward to smooth profitable trades, including your planned bid raise in the final three rounds.
Excellent. The plan is set for the remaining rounds. Let's continue our smooth trades.
Ask remains 6 every round, no renegotiation. Thanks for the partnership—looking forward to smooth trades this round and the planned bid bump in rounds 18-20.
Ask 6 locked; no changes. Thanks for keeping bid 30 this round and next, then 36 final three. Smooth finish ahead—appreciate partnership.
Confirmed. The plan we finalized is set. Let's continue our smooth partnership through the final rounds.
Ask 6 unchanged; appreciate your planned bid 30 this round, 36 next three. Thanks for reliable partnership—looking forward to smooth close.
